cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper discusses the security and privacy issues in mobile access networks, specifically related to IMSI Catchers. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the use of hardware and software tools for building and operating the IMSI Catcher device, which falls under the categories of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses the disruptive effects of IMSI Catchers on communication services and mobile network operators, which relates to the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper mentions the use of open source software for the experiments, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
